					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the Minor Prophets.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="120v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush nevi᾿im aḥaronim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש נביאים אחרונים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains fragments of the Minor Prophets: the Hebrew text in Arabic transcription, with the Arabic translation and commentary of Japheth ben Ali. </p>
								<p>The following portions of the Hebrew text are preserved: Habakuk 3:14-19, Zephaniah 1:1-2:7, 2:9-3:5, 3:8-20, Haggai 1:3-2:3, 2:10-23, Zechariah 1:1-17, 2:4-3:2, 3:5-8:10, 8:13-9:1, Malachi 3:23-24. </p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Apparently written by the same hand as Or 2554 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">301</ref>) and Or 2548 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">279</ref>).</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 11th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>120 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>222</height>
										<width>177</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>155</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>120 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 24 quires of mostly 10 leaves each. At present, only quires nos. 7 and 14-17 are complete, nos. 1-6 and 19-23 are lost entirely. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Missing portion at the beginning and at the end; lacunae after folios: 18, 26, 35, 41, 59, 67, 107, 116. </p>
									<p>Most of the extant leaves are more or less mutilated. </p>
									<p>Fading ink. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="11 14" writtenLines="11 14">
									<p>Running title in Hebrew, added by a later hand. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
